mons raphael Coots
bragge
mons: gisteren heb ul versuynt te adviseren dat ul soude gelieven
adriaen de Raes iognossement doen teeckenen over een pack no 25
met 75 tijken aen Toames pickering en leonard &obinson, daer en boven
een voor een packen NV met a 80 wit Eijnwaet van 12 stuyversdel
gead: aen abraham Vivian van londen, voor de tijcken volght
ierdificadie per naesten & naer groeteni te
London abraham Vivian
Antwerp 15 august 1682
S mij last to you was on the 12t unt sence non from you, so this onelyts
give you an aust. hou I finds the goods recd. viz: the 2 bales n 59 & 60
grove vire well andare sold all butt 4 p: n°61 and 62 prove in different,
bast rather to deare, because wee can nit make good intrest by then
for my order was from 3 ƒt a yd to 3:6 & 8 pence, that is butt for
some, and not that they all should be 3 7:8 & 9 pence, so there
in is agreat mistake & qni must wel. eafresly charge m. potter not
to aceed 3:6 pence butt all ander 3:6 or 7 pence, or alee wee cannet
to wel advance by them, our customus will not beston more then
42 stivers for dosino, & then they must be good soo stee have had dofins
ander 3:6 that were as good as these, m. potter must obserte the
breath for his dosins seld om hold but ¼ of nyd soth lists, endall
which is a great fault, & some northrens happento be so narroa to
sthers fore he mast toke an espetiall carito make them no less then
¼ of ayd broad with in the listo. n°63 with red & blee, are to 3 would
hate them, butt he bath bestowed to misch, wherifore order hants
send anothes baleto bon other 8 reds & 2 blews as they were butt he
should give nomore then 3:7 att finthest, & Rather less abordinghe
can meet with them I have sold 28 dosins 6 oeds & the 2 bleews, the bay
n' 64 proves agreat mistake, for I desired mint & red kersies, & yn
send mnt & red cloathes, for itt is no fort off kersie, bust a binde
of cloth, which is not proper for this countray, yet shall inde a tour to
dispose of them the white kersies in N67:68 & 69 are well, or on differenty
one fault in the 22 yds that yd freind hath not obleobed, my instracted
in thier beast for off the 22 y there is nostone excceding off ayd, & t
can sell non except they be ¼ of ay & 3 a 4 nches fall broad, so that
I shall have much a doto dispose off them. wee shall neverhave, soo
good kersies as we had from m. schpping: these see John holgoids
bought, & would hate yui do noncore with him, butt rather prceed
nith m. noter in all yd: concernes for & do muth feare the
neee man to, as I doubt by the past & prises my orders oft 2 may
ras was for 5 bales off dosins 3 bales of northrens from 3:10 to
4:4 & 5 bales off fine northrens from 4:6 to 5ƒ a yd. which
S supose are mot al bought, yet I hope my last order shall come in
fincto contromand some drap & calloins in eath bale, & to patt dar
grayes insteed & lett rather the silve grayes be futt by, for I finde by the
demand that one or 2 drap cullours on each bale will be enongd, because I
finde so good content in the northrens of abour 4 ƒ a yd. as n° 60 wase
would have you order m. Potter to buy 2 bales more of that sort, so then to be 5 bale
cloth In all, of that fort, as well as of the dosins, & fine broad cloathes, latt these 2
balet be assorted in cullours at the otlers onely 2 draps in each bale, the rest modich
e grayes as formerly mentioned: lively cullours, makes lively sale, there want 5
aertres M yd. & 55 of t0 yd. to compleat my order, which I hope will prove bede
then these now recs lett 10 white ones of each sort be bied red & ordered as saal
goods are u sually don up, to besent hether by them selves, as some as pou
Iave exspect the bays mentoned, & att least of each sort of cloathes one bale
by fm, for I sell as fast as Jear the remaindens, and shall sence forwaed
have no more goods scom the noour, butt from you, so that you will finde my
orders much larger, then ever before, & I hope the proffitt to boath our content
where fore desire m. Petter to do in endeavoair, & to observe orders with all ford
puncuallior, & advise mee, sow to ged. my self accordingly beeng
London Henry Maynard
C 15 aug 1682
In answer toyd of 28th past tis well what you ave don, about the bill of H. C
yd bill I have accepted, & shall be puncually fayd, & past to my acctt. I take not ce
that the turkey comp. sath ordered slupping, & that ther fore reds & whites will
rather advance, then deelyne, soas tis vere good you bought the reds & pack whiter
before that order come out: I could with you had bought some iwer. rd & E5 yallon
marchx also, yett I rope they ae rather less in prijse, esoever, lett them be what
they will provede of each sort 5 p p ven futto my custndrs do emplaine of the
last, as not beeng milled thich enougs, so pray endeavour to have good goods. the
goods from aboard mason an ben exspected within 2 3, god send klarck speedly
over, for swant the 6N. l other 5p first, I would dave you desire the makes
to make thene as formerly, for the lenght is not considdened, except itt be of the
same qualite, for our reverend fathers beleave, & an of opinon that what they
ue langee, could fare been milled in, & should hare ben to make them of forman
qualitie, & you know tis a sort of perple that an ven enming, so wee must
endeavour to please them, & itt will burne to our intrest. I do exspect the
spanish cloathes desired, for air demand & sale comes on a pace which will doubt
hets bring mony, to remitt you betder then retherte I have don you will do well
do pick up some spanish cloaches now & then to make up 2 bales according to
these inclosed patt. & prijses. I lope the red kersies will come in time with
smuch, for I do much want them, & seeng you feare that bayes will not prove
to content, I woild rather save you contramand them, jn good goods must do
our bustijnes. as for northren cloathes, in case you go to the neres I shall send you
patt. for one bale for a tryall, other wise desire to be excused, for I finde my sil fr served
from the noith to content, where as never yett could do much good upon y. I lave seom
you peither in gaine of proffitt, or reputation by selling. of yd nept please to advise
mee what the swanthins bayes sell, for the green & yallow streephes for I want 8 p
which I would have you buy, if to be had as formaly for 66. 67 a 68 s a good, thereby
25 of tersie cottons of about 40ƒ & 2d. of aboue 48ƒ butt if that com be risen to much
or deau as last Geare, so please to medele with non, except the wantkins bayes, which might
be packett amonghst the pack whites, or as you shall iudge convenient. inclosed acctt of
sale of last month, which please toepaimm a finding right notw accordingy & advise mee
